Seven elected Ukambani leaders have seven days to explain to the Wiper disciplinary committee why they should not be punished and expelled for being presumed to have resigned from the party.They are Machakos Governor Alfred Mutua, MPs Joe Mutambu (Mwingi Central) and Richard Makenga (Kaiti). Others are Nominated MP Robert Mutemi, Kilome s Regina Ndambuki, John Munuve (Mwingi North) and Kisoi Munyao (Mbooni).The leaders are required to respond to the show-cause letter within seven days or the disciplinary committee will take the next action without further notice. Mutua faces another accusation of forming or helping in the formation of a political party, while being a member of Wiper. He has formed the Maendeleo Chap Chap Movement, which has been registered as a political party.